Cassandra Quin Butts, a friend of President Obama and First Lady Michelle Obama, has passed away. The President and First Lady describe her as someone who inspired others to be better. They met Butts in law school and bonded over a shared passion for jazz and public service. Throughout her life, Butts worked in various positions, including on Capitol Hill, at the NAACP Legal Defense and Educational Fund, and as an advisor to the President. She was dedicated to advancing causes such as opportunity, civil rights, development, and democracy. Despite her young age, Butts made a significant impact on the lives of many. The President and First Lady express their admiration for her and the deep loss they feel.